title: Concussion rate in the U.S. 2010 to 2015 , by age
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Rate per 1,000 members, containing a total of 15 data points.
Overall Rate per 1,000 members has decreased over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 15-17_years and 18-19_years.
Maximum Rate per 1,000 members, about 18.8 was reported at Year 15-17_years
Minimum Rate per 1,000 members about 1.0 was reached at Year <1_year
